# Project Documentation (docs/)

**docs/** คือแหล่งรวมเอกสารสำหรับทำโปรเจกต์ ใช้ในการค้นข้อมูลและอัปเดตเอกสาร

**docs/** is the central project documentation. Use it to find information and to update documentation.

## When to use

- **Searching for project info:** Requirements, architecture, features, tech stack, and conventions live under `docs/`. Start from `docs/INDEX.md` for the mapping of split documents (structure/, core/, feature/).
- **Updating documentation:** Add or edit content under `docs/`. When you create or modify any file under `docs/`, follow the **docs-changelog** rule (update `docs/PRD_CHANGE_LOG.md`). See `.cursor/rules/docs-changelog.mdc` and `docs/RULE.md`.

## Quick reference

| Area        | Location in docs/ |
|------------|--------------------|
| Index      | `docs/INDEX.md`    |
| Source of truth | `docs/PRD.md`  |
| Structure  | `docs/structure/`  |
| Core       | `docs/core/`       |
| Features   | `docs/feature/`    |

When the user references **@docs** or asks about the project, prefer reading from `docs/` to answer.
